WEBVTT

00:16.809 --> 00:19.122
[CUTLERY RATTLING]

00:24.127 --> 00:26.336
[RAPID BANGING]

00:37.485 --> 00:40.178
[DOOR CREAKING]

00:50.119 --> 00:53.122
[CUTLERY SHAKING,
OBJECTS CRASHING]

00:58.955 --> 01:01.509
[GIRLS SCREAMING]

01:11.933 --> 01:14.177
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

01:29.468 --> 01:34.128
[HEAVY RUMBLING,
PEOPLE CLAMORING]

01:43.620 --> 01:46.692
[RUMBLING INTENSIFIES,
SCREAMING DISTORTS]

01:53.113 --> 01:54.631
[SILENCE]

02:08.782 --> 02:11.303
[DISTANT RUMBLING]

02:39.780 --> 02:40.815
WOMAN: Hey.

02:44.750 --> 02:45.889
Did anything fall on you?

02:49.583 --> 02:52.102
Shouldn't we call our parents?

02:52.137 --> 02:54.484
Just to let them know
we're okay.

02:57.349 --> 02:59.351
We were only shaking
a minute.

03:03.321 --> 03:04.977
Where is everyone else?

03:06.841 --> 03:07.946
Did they leave?

03:11.329 --> 03:12.640
Hey, what was your name again?

03:18.922 --> 03:20.407
[TO SELF] Olivia.

03:32.936 --> 03:34.248
Some call me Dolly.

03:36.664 --> 03:39.391
Everybody calls me that,
and I hat-- I hate that.

03:43.361 --> 03:45.225
You bring your doll to school?

03:47.157 --> 03:48.607
It's an antique.

03:49.988 --> 03:51.921
It's not like it's a toy
or anything.

03:54.061 --> 03:55.821
-Dolly...
-No, don't.

03:58.514 --> 04:00.688
Don't tell the other girls,
okay?

04:03.898 --> 04:06.625
Wasn't so long ago
we were all playing with dolls.

04:17.257 --> 04:19.293
[RATTLING]

04:20.156 --> 04:22.089
-Oh, shit.
-[DOLLY YELPS]

04:22.123 --> 04:24.022
Hey, come on, clean up.

04:27.336 --> 04:29.890
[GULPS] No way.

04:31.063 --> 04:32.444
Up to you.

04:35.689 --> 04:38.036
I don't wanna get my dress wet.

04:38.070 --> 04:39.348
Take your dress off.

04:42.834 --> 04:44.801
I don't even know you.

04:44.836 --> 04:46.872
What do you think you have
that I haven't seen?

04:49.944 --> 04:52.947
I'm not getting naked.

04:54.259 --> 04:55.985
What, are you on your period
or something?

04:58.228 --> 04:59.437
Probably.

05:01.853 --> 05:03.475
Okay, well, sorry.

05:06.616 --> 05:08.377
I mean,

05:08.411 --> 05:11.034
it's not like I'm afraid
of water or anything.

05:11.690 --> 05:13.865
I mean, I shower every night.

05:13.899 --> 05:16.039
I'm pretty sure that's
what my aunt taught me.

05:18.387 --> 05:19.595
My step-dad taught me.

05:19.629 --> 05:23.012
He teaches me everything,
he taught me how to dive.

05:23.046 --> 05:26.602
And if he's okay, I bet
he's gonna come after us,
'cause he's basically a fireman.

05:32.159 --> 05:33.954
I saw a house on fire once.

05:35.369 --> 05:36.577
In Malibu.

05:40.443 --> 05:42.480
The whole mountain
was burning.

05:44.447 --> 05:47.347
And there was a house on top
of that mountain and...

05:48.555 --> 05:49.901
It was burning too.

05:53.594 --> 05:55.424
I watched it burn down
to nothing.

06:00.636 --> 06:03.397
I'm-I'm sure there was
nobody inside.

06:06.296 --> 06:07.712
I'm sure your stepdad will come.

06:08.989 --> 06:10.059
Hmm.

06:13.407 --> 06:16.065
I mean,
everyone knows we're here.

06:16.099 --> 06:18.619
-Of course they do,
they dropped us off.
-Right, of course.

06:26.696 --> 06:28.733
Do you hear sirens though?

06:30.424 --> 06:31.908
Like in the distance?

06:34.463 --> 06:36.396
I don't hear anything but you.

06:37.466 --> 06:40.572
Right, but... [STUTTERING]

06:40.607 --> 06:42.781
I mean,
shouldn't we hear sirens?

06:44.127 --> 06:46.440
We should at least
hear something.

06:46.475 --> 06:50.375
I mean, my aunt lives
in the valley and
she hears sirens all night,

06:50.410 --> 06:52.550
and helicopters
at four in the morning.

06:53.861 --> 06:55.829
OLIVIA: You know, it's good
that we don't hear anything.

06:57.313 --> 06:58.556
Maybe.

06:59.557 --> 07:03.146
Like... nothing too terrible
has happened.

07:07.599 --> 07:10.015
But what if he isn't okay?

07:11.292 --> 07:14.468
Your stepfather, I mean
we were shaking for a while...

07:14.503 --> 07:16.436
-He's fine.
-...and what if our parents

07:16.470 --> 07:19.956
aren't coming to rescue us
because they need someone
to rescue them.

07:21.441 --> 07:24.478
I mean,
I don't wanna be dramatic,

07:24.513 --> 07:26.722
[GULPS] but it looks like
we're trapped.

07:27.757 --> 07:30.864
[STAMMERING] Can we
even find a way out?

07:30.898 --> 07:33.176
we're still shaking
a little bit, aren't we?

07:33.211 --> 07:34.730
We'll find a way out, yeah.

07:40.390 --> 07:41.495
What if...

07:42.323 --> 07:43.773
What about the roads?

07:44.636 --> 07:46.396
I mean, what if...

07:46.431 --> 07:49.469
what if we don't hear
the sirens because

07:49.503 --> 07:51.574
all the policemen are dead.

07:51.609 --> 07:54.474
I mean, is that possible?
[STAMMERING]

07:54.508 --> 07:56.855
That everyone out there
is in so much trouble,

07:56.890 --> 08:01.032
but we-we're in
the worst trouble
because we're in here...

08:01.066 --> 08:02.171
alone.

08:06.347 --> 08:07.970
I don't even know you.

08:13.458 --> 08:14.701
Look.

08:15.909 --> 08:18.118
It's the reflection
from the chandelier.

08:25.677 --> 08:28.266
Whoa! It's wrecked in here.

08:28.300 --> 08:30.026
DOLLY: We know that.

08:30.061 --> 08:31.131
How do you guys feel?

08:32.097 --> 08:33.616
OLIVIA: Not hurt.

08:33.650 --> 08:36.688
Oh, no, I don't mean physically.
This is stressful.

08:36.722 --> 08:38.138
Do either of you smoke?

08:38.172 --> 08:39.277
No, it's disgusting.

08:41.174 --> 08:42.211
You?

08:43.764 --> 08:49.321
[DOOR KNOB JIGGLING,
BANGING]

08:56.052 --> 08:58.123
You were gonna let me
suffocate in here, I know it.

09:01.679 --> 09:02.921
Where'd you get that?

09:04.164 --> 09:06.028
The chandelier.

09:08.893 --> 09:10.964
Why are you all just
hanging around?

09:21.561 --> 09:22.872
Eden...

09:26.220 --> 09:27.290
What do you think?

09:28.360 --> 09:29.569
Do you know where your mom is?

09:30.466 --> 09:33.262
Do you know when
she's gonna be back?

09:33.296 --> 09:37.162
We know about the front door,
we know about the cellar door.
Are there any other doors?

09:37.197 --> 09:38.750
That's a stupid question.

09:38.785 --> 09:41.546
Of course, there's another
way out, and we're finding it,
so everyone up.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.168
-Right?
-No.

09:44.584 --> 09:47.690
DOLLY: The house
isn't exactly stable, right

09:47.725 --> 09:50.866
because we're literally
underground.

09:52.212 --> 09:54.007
We don't have running water.

09:55.422 --> 09:56.768
PIPER: We shouldn't split up.

09:57.389 --> 09:59.219
I don't see anything.

09:59.253 --> 10:01.359
Okay, well, some of us
will go look in the bedroom,

10:01.393 --> 10:02.809
and some of us will stay here.

10:03.568 --> 10:05.018
What are we looking for?

10:07.607 --> 10:09.643
This is all just to keep us
from panicking.

10:09.678 --> 10:10.817
[BREATHING ECHOES]

10:13.267 --> 10:14.752
WOMAN: Happy Birthday, Annie.

10:35.738 --> 10:37.947
[CRIES IN FRUSTRATION]

10:42.296 --> 10:44.885
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

10:51.271 --> 10:53.411
[CAT PURRING SOFTLY]

10:55.689 --> 10:57.587
I used to have a cat like this.

10:57.622 --> 11:00.901
Oh, yeah?
Cats steal your breathe
while you're sleeping.

11:04.008 --> 11:05.872
[PANTING]

11:06.562 --> 11:07.839
[GASPING]

11:08.598 --> 11:10.704
[HISSES, MEOWS]

11:10.739 --> 11:13.673
[WHIMPERING] Stop. Stop it.

11:14.363 --> 11:15.916
You bitches scared it away.

11:18.505 --> 11:20.887
[BREATHING SLOWING DOWN]

11:28.239 --> 11:31.104
[CRASHES, CRIES OUT]

11:31.138 --> 11:34.694
[CRYING LOUDLY]

11:37.869 --> 11:40.009
[SOBBING] Oh, my God.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.755
[SQUEALING]

12:02.342 --> 12:04.516
This is not an exit.

12:04.551 --> 12:06.242
It's broken.

12:08.313 --> 12:09.832
It's broken.

12:09.867 --> 12:12.041
It's broken. It's broken.

12:12.939 --> 12:14.734
It's broken. It's broken.

12:14.768 --> 12:15.942
I told her not to.

12:15.976 --> 12:17.529
Well, I'm independent.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.814
Forget about the bedrooms,

12:25.848 --> 12:27.781
or trying to squeeze through
any of the windows...

12:32.406 --> 12:33.511
We can't get out.

12:39.103 --> 12:41.830
-We even saw--
-We're gonna be here
a lot longer than an hour?

12:43.624 --> 12:44.971
We're gonna be here for a while.

12:46.110 --> 12:49.907
[ALL TALKING OVER EACH OTHER]

12:51.840 --> 12:54.187
Hey. Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

12:55.982 --> 13:00.020
You can't talk without
the crystal.

13:00.400 --> 13:01.781
Okay?

13:01.815 --> 13:04.887
'Cause otherwise then
everybody talks once

13:04.922 --> 13:08.028
-and then nobody listens.
-This is just like school.

13:08.063 --> 13:10.272
This is just as oppressive
as school.

13:13.447 --> 13:14.483
Here.

13:15.415 --> 13:16.588
Take it.

13:17.417 --> 13:18.590
Take charge.

13:22.353 --> 13:23.354
I'll do it.

13:27.461 --> 13:28.428
No.

13:30.602 --> 13:31.914
No one wants to.

13:32.570 --> 13:34.227
-Default.
-[CHUCKLES]

13:34.261 --> 13:36.539
-Democracy.
-Like that even works.

13:38.921 --> 13:41.510
I honestly don't trust
any of you.

13:45.928 --> 13:47.274
We can vote.

13:48.448 --> 13:51.761
We don't need a leader,
we can all be equal.

13:51.796 --> 13:54.143
I-I nominate Olivia.

13:54.868 --> 13:56.697
I nominate me.

13:56.732 --> 13:58.838
-[CHUCKLES]
-Okay.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.565
Who votes for Piper?

14:06.535 --> 14:09.365
Now, who votes for Olivia?

14:16.441 --> 14:18.098
We're her friend.

14:18.512 --> 14:19.548
Right?

14:23.517 --> 14:24.933
Just for a couple of hours.

14:28.281 --> 14:29.282
Countdown.

14:45.505 --> 14:48.439
Looks like we're pretty solid
though the weekend.

14:48.473 --> 14:51.062
-Na-uh.
-I'm not wasting
the whole weekend here.

14:51.097 --> 14:53.720
Just don't touch anything
or don't do anything.

14:53.754 --> 14:55.515
Don't use anything
until you have to.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.795
Or we can just...

14:59.829 --> 15:02.315
manifest a rescue.

15:11.462 --> 15:12.497
Turn the phones off.

15:13.705 --> 15:15.155
-Why?
-To save battery.

15:15.190 --> 15:17.502
Who cares? They don't work.

15:17.537 --> 15:20.954
Yes, they do. It's just that
we don't have any bars.

15:21.990 --> 15:23.439
Mine's no different.

15:25.579 --> 15:27.340
We turn the phones on
for a second and see

15:27.374 --> 15:29.790
if anyone has called, or texted,
or check the bars.

15:29.825 --> 15:31.516
But then we have to
turn them off.

15:33.346 --> 15:35.313
But turning them on an off
wastes the power.

15:37.039 --> 15:38.696
Just don't let the phones die.

15:41.802 --> 15:43.597
Do you know anything
about electricity?

15:46.738 --> 15:48.740
I know the lights weren't on.

15:48.775 --> 15:49.983
Duh, if the light were--

15:50.018 --> 15:52.882
I have the crystal,
so it's my turn.

15:52.917 --> 15:57.163
And I know the lights aren't on,
but I did see the box
where you...

15:57.197 --> 16:00.338
-You flip the... [STUTTERING]
-You... You... [MIMICKING]

16:11.971 --> 16:14.283
Me, Amanda, and Mallory
are the eldest,

16:14.318 --> 16:16.251
so we will take care
of the phones,

16:16.285 --> 16:19.668
and go through all the bedrooms
to make sure they're empty.

16:19.702 --> 16:21.428
We'll keep everyone safe.

16:22.050 --> 16:23.534
OLIVIA: I agree with "safe."

16:23.568 --> 16:24.673
We're not safe.

16:27.572 --> 16:29.126
I saw someone.

16:36.616 --> 16:37.893
I saw them.

16:37.927 --> 16:39.584
No, you didn't.

16:39.619 --> 16:40.654
We were in every room.

16:41.586 --> 16:42.587
Were we?

16:43.726 --> 16:45.728
Eden, there's no one here
but us.

16:45.763 --> 16:49.663
They were coming at me
when everything's still shaking.

16:51.907 --> 16:54.013
-A boy?
-A man.

16:54.047 --> 16:55.393
They were making these sounds.

16:56.394 --> 16:58.017
They were saying something.

16:59.018 --> 17:01.123
Not my name, but these sounds.

17:03.539 --> 17:04.575
OLIVIA: Eden...

17:05.748 --> 17:07.128
how do we get outside?

17:08.682 --> 17:10.063
[SIGHS]

17:10.443 --> 17:11.547
He's inside.

17:17.897 --> 17:19.348
[CLICKING SWITCH]

17:20.762 --> 17:21.763
It's a blackout.

17:26.942 --> 17:28.253
We need power.

17:29.565 --> 17:32.154
We need to try the breakers
like we tried the phones.

17:33.673 --> 17:35.054
Promise?

17:35.088 --> 17:35.985
-Yeah.
-I-I promise.

17:36.020 --> 17:37.125
-Sure.
-Yeah.

18:55.858 --> 18:57.481
[SIGHS]

19:08.216 --> 19:09.665
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

19:12.289 --> 19:15.223
[EERIE VOCAL
HARMONIZING PLAYING]

19:35.829 --> 19:36.968
[BREATH TREMBLING]

19:59.750 --> 20:01.303
Ready?

20:01.338 --> 20:03.961
ALL: Happy Birthday, Eden.

20:09.242 --> 20:10.795
Let's divide the piece up.

20:12.072 --> 20:13.350
Evenly.

20:15.697 --> 20:17.043
There's crackers.

20:17.077 --> 20:18.631
And diet soda.

20:21.668 --> 20:22.945
I saw chardonnay.

20:34.509 --> 20:36.304
[HUMMING]

20:57.359 --> 20:59.706
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

21:15.377 --> 21:18.725
[EERIE VOCAL
HARMONIZING PLAYING]

21:42.715 --> 21:44.993
[ALL HUMMING]

21:46.995 --> 21:48.341
[LAUGHS]

21:50.516 --> 21:52.863
-[LAUGHS, GASPS]
-[RUMBLING]

21:52.897 --> 21:54.899
It's an aftershock.

21:54.934 --> 21:56.660
The Santa Anas! CHUCKLES]

21:56.694 --> 22:00.180
-[PLAYFULLY] Ohh, meteorites!
-[WHOOPS]

22:00.215 --> 22:01.872
[ALL LAUGHING]

22:06.428 --> 22:08.844
[LAUGHING EXCITEDLY]

22:19.752 --> 22:20.856
What's that?

22:22.962 --> 22:23.894
Hmm...

22:24.308 --> 22:25.344
Uh.

22:30.556 --> 22:34.698
[SCREAMING, CRYING]

22:34.732 --> 22:36.976
It's fine, look. It's fine.

22:38.184 --> 22:40.359
[WHIMPERING, CRYING]

22:40.393 --> 22:41.808
We're fine.

22:44.397 --> 22:46.675
-We're fine.
-[CRYING]

22:55.235 --> 22:57.134
[WIND HOWLING SOFTLY]

23:03.071 --> 23:05.694
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]

23:08.456 --> 23:10.665
[WHIMPERS]

23:10.699 --> 23:13.012
-Let her go.
-What? I mean, come...

23:15.014 --> 23:16.636
[CONTINUES CRYING]

23:20.778 --> 23:22.780
[GIRLS LAUGHING]

23:23.402 --> 23:24.851
What's your problem?

23:31.617 --> 23:33.619
Someone go check the phones
and the box.

23:34.309 --> 23:35.828
Eden already did that.

23:37.554 --> 23:39.176
Eden already did that, trust me.

23:40.867 --> 23:42.006
Eden?

23:45.424 --> 23:46.701
Eden?

23:51.637 --> 23:53.155
-Eden?
-Look out.

23:53.190 --> 23:54.709
[DOLLY CONTINUES CRYING]

23:54.743 --> 23:55.882
Eden?

23:58.816 --> 23:59.679
Eden?

24:01.129 --> 24:02.199
Eden?

24:04.753 --> 24:05.789
Eden?

24:10.207 --> 24:11.864
-Eden?
-[WHIMPERING]

24:12.899 --> 24:13.969
Eden?

24:30.538 --> 24:33.230
Whoa. What is this?

24:38.373 --> 24:39.478
Oh...

24:40.237 --> 24:41.272
it feels funny.

24:44.310 --> 24:45.553
[DOOR CREAKS]

24:45.587 --> 24:47.140
It smells sweet.

24:49.280 --> 24:50.627
[GIGGLES]

24:56.460 --> 24:57.599
Eden?

25:05.227 --> 25:06.194
Eden?

25:13.304 --> 25:14.547
Eden?

25:17.136 --> 25:18.171
Eden?

25:20.277 --> 25:23.280
Let's just not let
any negative energy intervene.

25:26.559 --> 25:27.802
Yeah.

25:30.045 --> 25:31.219
I mean...

25:32.116 --> 25:34.774
This could mean that
Eden got outside.

25:34.809 --> 25:36.535
Eden's never been outside.

25:39.745 --> 25:42.023
Has anyone ever seen
Eden outside?

25:46.234 --> 25:47.856
No.

25:47.891 --> 25:50.203
She knew a secret door
or some shit,

25:50.238 --> 25:51.929
and she left us here.

26:00.938 --> 26:02.043
Maybe.

26:03.562 --> 26:04.942
Maybe.

26:06.150 --> 26:07.980
[CAT MEOWING]

26:14.607 --> 26:16.022
You hear that?

26:18.507 --> 26:19.785
It attacked me.

26:22.442 --> 26:24.893
I thought we only had to worry
about the man. But...

26:26.032 --> 26:28.069
looks like
there's an animal too.

26:28.103 --> 26:29.311
There is no man.

26:30.105 --> 26:31.175
There is a man.

26:33.177 --> 26:34.938
Eden saw him, and...

26:36.318 --> 26:37.872
he knows there are girls here.

26:43.429 --> 26:47.260
Some of us still have a "V"
to lose.

26:52.852 --> 26:56.235
Oh, don't say shit like that!

26:56.269 --> 26:59.894
Do you want them to think
that a man's gonna come in here?

26:59.928 --> 27:00.791
[SNIGGERS]

27:03.829 --> 27:06.659
Dolly can barely hold
a pair of scissors.

27:08.557 --> 27:10.076
That's not my problem.

27:10.698 --> 27:12.631
All of our problem.

27:18.844 --> 27:21.156
Do you really think
Eden saw someone?

27:22.571 --> 27:23.745
A man?

27:24.263 --> 27:25.747
Yes, Piper, a man.

27:25.782 --> 27:29.337
We can't ask her
because she's gone, isn't she?

27:35.723 --> 27:37.241
[CHUCKLES]

27:38.208 --> 27:39.796
So Olivia...

27:42.384 --> 27:44.214
thinks I'm scaring you...

27:46.457 --> 27:48.356
by talking about the man.

27:51.290 --> 27:53.257
But we're not little girls.

28:06.167 --> 28:07.340
We're women.

28:17.454 --> 28:21.078
[WOMAN VOCALIZING RHYTHMICALLY]

28:43.273 --> 28:45.862
[VOCALS HARMONIZING
AND BUILD IN TEMPO]

29:18.515 --> 29:19.550
So ugly.

29:22.588 --> 29:27.248
I mean, I know you're not
supposed to say that
about art, but...

29:28.974 --> 29:30.769
But it's really ugly.

29:30.803 --> 29:33.047
Yeah, but...

29:33.081 --> 29:35.808
Don't you think you need
a little ugliness?

29:35.843 --> 29:38.949
Some beauty's empty,
it's like oppressive.

29:38.984 --> 29:41.952
People think that everything
needs to be beautiful, but

29:41.987 --> 29:44.679
beauty is our baggage.

29:44.713 --> 29:47.544
Like pink, how pink is pretty
but not when it's in my hair.

29:52.480 --> 29:54.516
I never really liked pink.

29:56.449 --> 29:57.968
My favorite color's green.

29:58.003 --> 30:00.281
Then you should
dye your hair green.

30:02.870 --> 30:04.872
Yeah, well...

30:04.906 --> 30:06.563
my other favorite color's grey.

30:07.736 --> 30:08.979
No one's favorite color is grey.

30:09.014 --> 30:11.050
Grey's the ugliest color
that there is.

30:12.017 --> 30:14.053
Unless if you see
beauty in the ugly.

30:18.989 --> 30:20.439
I never really thought about it.

30:21.750 --> 30:23.994
They've never tell you
about what this is?

30:25.616 --> 30:26.514
No.

30:27.480 --> 30:29.034
It's from German mythology.

30:29.966 --> 30:32.244
Frauenweltmeans
"the lady world."

30:35.661 --> 30:37.283
A beautiful woman
from the front

30:37.318 --> 30:40.252
and her back is covered
in puss and maggots.

30:40.286 --> 30:42.668
Personally I don't appreciate
the metaphor.

30:42.702 --> 30:44.843
[WOMAN VOCALIZING, ECHOING]

30:49.882 --> 30:53.541
[WOMEN VOCALIZING IN CACOPHONY]

31:47.112 --> 31:49.079
What time did you get in?

31:56.397 --> 31:57.501
Late.

32:08.029 --> 32:10.100
You were kicking all night.

32:15.105 --> 32:16.969
I had a bad dream.

32:28.981 --> 32:30.431
About what?

32:40.613 --> 32:42.063
I don't remember.

32:50.692 --> 32:52.211
But I'm thirsty.

32:53.661 --> 32:55.559
I'm really, really thirsty.

33:10.850 --> 33:12.162
OLIVIA: Morning.

33:14.337 --> 33:15.407
Wake.

33:18.479 --> 33:19.687
Morning and wake.

33:23.035 --> 33:24.933
Two words to describe

33:24.968 --> 33:27.626
the beginning of the day...

33:27.660 --> 33:29.076
and the end of our lives.

33:32.113 --> 33:33.563
What'd you dream about?

33:37.394 --> 33:38.533
Nothing.

33:40.225 --> 33:43.055
I squeezed my eyes
and tried to dream about Eden.

33:49.648 --> 33:51.477
What are we supposed to do?

33:53.479 --> 33:54.515
I don't know.

33:56.137 --> 33:57.690
What are we supposed to do?

33:57.725 --> 33:59.830
[WOMEN VOCALIZING RHYTHMICALLY]

34:11.324 --> 34:12.705
PIPER:
This is pretty boring, huh?

34:15.949 --> 34:17.226
Boring's fine.

34:17.262 --> 34:18.780
Boring is the worst.

34:19.609 --> 34:20.748
The worst.

34:35.245 --> 34:37.351
PIPER: I wonder if the man
can hear us.

34:40.837 --> 34:42.356
I'm not playing that game.

34:44.150 --> 34:45.462
What game?

34:47.014 --> 34:48.741
Whatever it is you're doing.

34:50.743 --> 34:51.744
I'm just saying.

34:53.746 --> 34:55.851
OLIVIA: Right.

34:55.886 --> 34:58.579
PIPER: This party would be
a lot more fun
if boys were here.

34:58.613 --> 34:59.752
[OLIVIA SCOFFS]

35:01.927 --> 35:04.861
OLIVIA: This party would be a lot more fun if it were over.

35:04.895 --> 35:05.758
[PIPER SCOFFS]

35:08.589 --> 35:09.762
You don't like me.

35:10.487 --> 35:12.558
It's cool, you don't have to.

35:15.596 --> 35:18.185
You know my mom says that
girls never really
like each other

35:18.219 --> 35:19.669
because we're too competitive.

35:21.464 --> 35:22.568
[CHUCKLES]

35:25.019 --> 35:26.503
Who? You and your mom?

35:28.367 --> 35:29.472
Maybe.

35:36.375 --> 35:37.825
OLIVIA: My stepfather...

35:40.345 --> 35:42.588
always says that

35:42.623 --> 35:45.212
pretty girls just want to be told that they're smart,

35:46.523 --> 35:49.561
and smart girls
just want to be told
that they're pretty.

35:51.114 --> 35:52.633
And that's why
we're never happy.

35:54.117 --> 35:55.601
That's why
we never like each other

35:55.636 --> 35:58.397
because we just want
boys approval.

36:00.088 --> 36:02.436
[PIPER CHUCKLES]

36:02.470 --> 36:04.679
PIPER: Well, I hope he's not
a guidance counselor.

36:05.611 --> 36:07.372
OLIVIA: He's
a volunteer fireman.

36:09.615 --> 36:10.478
PIPER: Well...

36:12.204 --> 36:14.033
I think it's fine to be mean
if you're smart,

36:14.068 --> 36:17.313
and obviously I think
it's fine to mean
if you're pretty.

36:21.282 --> 36:22.766
You could just be nice.

36:25.217 --> 36:27.254
You could be anything to anyone.

36:44.892 --> 36:47.619
[VOCALIZING]

36:50.553 --> 36:52.451
[IMITATES PHONE RINGING]
Brr-ing, brr-ing.

36:54.108 --> 36:56.455
Brr-ing, brr-ing.

37:00.425 --> 37:01.495
Hey.

37:02.875 --> 37:05.602
I'm just calling to let you know
I'm not coming in to work today.

37:07.570 --> 37:09.606
It isn't because
I'm being irresponsible.

37:12.954 --> 37:14.508
It isn't because I'm sick...

37:16.682 --> 37:18.684
and it isn't because
I couldn't get a ride.

37:20.824 --> 37:23.379
It's because
something horrible has happened.

37:26.623 --> 37:29.385
Which you probably already know
because you're dead.

37:39.257 --> 37:40.637
Do you think it's war?

37:45.055 --> 37:47.920
Anyway, sorry.

37:48.749 --> 37:49.612
Thank you.

37:50.854 --> 37:51.855
Bye.

37:55.790 --> 37:56.791
Boop.

38:06.836 --> 38:08.424
[EXHALES]

38:15.914 --> 38:16.777
[SIGHS]

38:39.075 --> 38:40.835
[URINATING]

39:03.341 --> 39:04.963
[OPENS CUPBOARD DOOR]

39:25.466 --> 39:27.054
[BOTTLE CAP FALLS]

40:16.931 --> 40:18.588
[WOOD CREAKING]

40:26.458 --> 40:27.563
[SIGHS]

40:28.909 --> 40:30.220
[URINATING]

40:32.222 --> 40:34.466
MALLORY: Piper wants you
to stay in the living room.

40:39.644 --> 40:42.474
I'm allowed to go anywhere.

40:47.962 --> 40:49.032
[WHISPERS INAUDIBLY]

40:49.067 --> 40:50.517
What are you talking about?

40:58.421 --> 40:59.836
Is it the man?

41:02.874 --> 41:05.117
You think you could escape him?

41:10.122 --> 41:11.538
He...

41:11.572 --> 41:14.575
[TREMBLING]
He doesn't want me.

41:15.369 --> 41:16.991
I'm just a little girl.

41:19.304 --> 41:20.581
You said it.

41:21.548 --> 41:24.102
[LAUGHING, GIGGLING]

41:29.072 --> 41:32.110
[HELICOPTER HOVERING]

41:32.144 --> 41:34.733
[SHUSHES]

41:42.776 --> 41:45.606
Help. Help. Help. Help.

41:45.641 --> 41:48.989
Help! Help! Help!

41:49.023 --> 41:52.199
-Here we are. Help! Help!
-[LAUGHING]

41:52.233 --> 41:55.616
-[LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY]
-[DOLLY CONTINUES SHOUTING]

41:58.343 --> 42:01.242
[HELICOPTER APPROACHING]

42:02.312 --> 42:04.970
ALL: Help! Help! Help! Help!

42:06.006 --> 42:07.835
Help! Please!

42:08.318 --> 42:10.251
Help!

42:12.840 --> 42:14.773
-[GASPING FOR BREATHE]
-[HELICOPTER FADING AWAY]

42:15.947 --> 42:17.638
[GIGGLING]

42:18.294 --> 42:20.641
DOLLY: Please! Help!

42:22.298 --> 42:24.127
Help. Help.

42:25.335 --> 42:26.958
Help. Help.

42:27.993 --> 42:30.755
[SOBBING] Help.

42:30.789 --> 42:32.342
They'll come back around.

42:32.860 --> 42:34.793
[PANTING]

42:34.828 --> 42:37.209
[LAUGHTER CONTINUES
IN OTHER ROOM]

42:39.177 --> 42:40.730
Where is everyone?

42:43.630 --> 42:45.321
You all stink.

42:52.639 --> 42:54.088
And whoever...

42:55.642 --> 42:58.058
peed in the toilet...

42:59.680 --> 43:01.268
is a stinky pig.

43:01.993 --> 43:02.994
Dead.

43:04.616 --> 43:05.617
Dead.

43:05.652 --> 43:06.894
It's dead.

43:08.586 --> 43:10.173
It's dead.

43:10.208 --> 43:12.279
-Dead.
-Stinky pig.

43:13.073 --> 43:14.833
Dead. Dead.

43:14.868 --> 43:17.491
-It's dead.
-Dead.

43:17.525 --> 43:19.631
-Dead.
-Stinky pig.

43:19.666 --> 43:23.946
-Dead.
-Dead. Dead. Dead.

43:24.256 --> 43:25.395
Dead!

43:27.812 --> 43:29.296
[SIGHS IN EXASPERATION]

43:30.884 --> 43:34.094
I don't mean to upset anyone

43:34.128 --> 43:35.405
but we're stranded.

43:37.269 --> 43:40.928
And I don't mean to blame anyone
but you let the phones die.

43:45.623 --> 43:47.383
The electricity
hasn't come back.

43:51.387 --> 43:53.078
We're hungry and we're thirsty,

43:53.113 --> 43:55.115
the phones suck,
the toilets suck,

43:55.149 --> 43:58.083
we ate birthday cake
for breakfast.

44:01.673 --> 44:02.985
Party's over.

44:03.399 --> 44:04.780
The party?

44:07.955 --> 44:10.958
We had only a few jobs.

44:12.201 --> 44:15.307
Check the boxes,
check the phones,
stay close.

44:15.342 --> 44:17.724
-Like how Eden stayed close.
-[STIFLES LAUGH]

44:20.623 --> 44:22.004
Why would you say that?

44:25.973 --> 44:28.113
[SOBBING]
That's offensive.

44:28.769 --> 44:32.083
Eden could be lost out there.

44:32.117 --> 44:34.775
Or she could be hurt
or even...

44:34.810 --> 44:36.812
Eden could have been killed.

44:40.747 --> 44:43.301
Oh, so now you believe
in the man?

44:45.268 --> 44:47.719
Yes, I believe in the man.

44:49.410 --> 44:50.791
I believe

44:50.826 --> 44:53.276
in everything you're saying.

44:53.311 --> 44:56.521
And so if you say that
there's something worse than us

44:56.555 --> 44:58.350
shaking,

44:58.385 --> 45:01.940
[STUTTERING] or our parents
being so hurt

45:01.975 --> 45:04.978
where that they can't come
rescue us, okay.

45:05.012 --> 45:08.222
Then I believe you,
and if you say

45:08.257 --> 45:12.364
that there's a man here
who wants to have sex with us,

45:12.399 --> 45:15.713
then I believe you, okay?
[HOARSELY] We're trapped!

45:16.610 --> 45:19.786
So if a helicopter comes by,

45:19.820 --> 45:22.581
you can't just be playing okay!
We're women,

45:22.616 --> 45:24.480
and we need you act like it!

45:25.412 --> 45:28.242
[LAUGHING]

45:28.277 --> 45:29.899
Why is that funny?

45:31.729 --> 45:33.351
Why is this funny?

45:34.490 --> 45:36.526
-[LAUGHING]
-Why is that funny!

45:37.355 --> 45:39.495
Why is this funny!

45:39.529 --> 45:42.774
-[LAUGHING]
-Why is this... [SCREAMS]

45:46.467 --> 45:48.090
-[LAUGHING]
-[SOBS]

45:50.023 --> 45:51.714
You know what you're being?

45:51.749 --> 45:53.474
-A mean--
-Pathetic.

45:54.475 --> 45:56.512
I was gonna say pathetic.

45:57.547 --> 45:59.515
You're being a little brat.

46:07.178 --> 46:08.869
I'm sorry.

46:08.904 --> 46:10.595
[VOICES ECHOING]
Brat... Pathetic...

46:10.629 --> 46:11.941
I said I'm sorry.

46:11.976 --> 46:13.909
[ECHOING]
You're being a brat,
being pathetic.

46:13.943 --> 46:16.325
I said I'm being sorry!

46:17.844 --> 46:20.536
I said... I said I'm sorry.

46:21.468 --> 46:23.366
They chose me, Piper.

46:24.851 --> 46:26.369
Can you deal with it?

46:36.897 --> 46:38.796
[DOLLY CRYING]

46:44.594 --> 46:46.493
Maybe another helicopter
will come.

46:47.494 --> 46:48.875
We could make a signal.

46:51.256 --> 46:53.327
We could all scream
at the same time.

46:53.362 --> 46:55.088
-It's never coming back.
-Every 15 minutes.

46:55.122 --> 46:58.505
-It's never coming back.
-Shh!

47:04.373 --> 47:05.236
[SIGHS]

47:11.449 --> 47:12.312
[EXHALES]

47:34.713 --> 47:36.163
[SOBS]

47:56.459 --> 47:57.357
[CRYING]

48:03.397 --> 48:04.260
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

48:13.373 --> 48:15.271
[SNORTS AND HAWKS]

48:36.568 --> 48:37.431
[SNORTS]

48:39.502 --> 48:40.365
[HAWKS]

48:42.609 --> 48:43.472
[SPITS, GRUNTS]

48:52.895 --> 48:55.415
[WOMEN VOCALIZING]

49:02.801 --> 49:03.664
[CAT TRILLS]

49:24.513 --> 49:25.376
[CLEARS THROAT]

49:36.490 --> 49:41.737
PIPER: [SINGING SOFTLY]
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

49:43.049 --> 49:48.399
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands ♪

49:50.056 --> 49:51.091
Hear that?

49:53.024 --> 49:55.268
That's our stomachs growling.

49:55.302 --> 50:00.100
PIPER: ♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

50:00.135 --> 50:05.692
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

50:06.693 --> 50:12.112
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands ♪

50:12.388 --> 50:13.769
Meeting.

50:13.803 --> 50:15.598
Dining room. Now.

50:18.153 --> 50:22.433
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands ♪

50:22.467 --> 50:25.229
-OLIVIA: I am sick
of the crystal. It's done.
-ROMY: No. It isn't.

50:25.263 --> 50:26.816
-PIPER: Then let's vote.
-No.

50:26.851 --> 50:29.750
No, we're not voting.
Put your hands down.
We need the crystal

50:29.785 --> 50:32.995
and we need the meetings
and we need the rules or else
we're not going to survive.

50:33.030 --> 50:34.859
♪ Ladies of the canyon
Our own land ♪

50:34.893 --> 50:37.931
OLIVIA: How long do you
think you can go without water?

50:37.965 --> 50:39.622
We're dirty. We're so dirty.

50:39.657 --> 50:42.004
-Everything is so dirty.
-ROMY: We're in trouble.

50:42.039 --> 50:43.868
PIPER: We were
in trouble anyways.

50:43.902 --> 50:45.318
The man stalking us.

50:45.352 --> 50:47.182
[CONTINUES SINGING]
♪ Our own land

50:47.216 --> 50:50.219
OLIVIA: New rule.
No one mentions the man.

50:50.668 --> 50:51.565
There is no man.

50:51.600 --> 50:53.257
-PIPER: You don't
make the rules.
-I do.

50:53.291 --> 50:57.088
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

50:57.123 --> 51:00.747
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands ♪

51:00.781 --> 51:01.955
PIPER: We're all scared of him.

51:01.989 --> 51:03.646
ROMY: We should only
be scared of each other.

51:03.681 --> 51:05.441
PIPER: We aren't
the ones who killed Eden.

51:06.408 --> 51:08.272
OLIVIA: No one killed Eden.

51:08.306 --> 51:10.412
DOLLY: She probably
just wandered off.

51:10.446 --> 51:12.793
And if she wandered off,
where did she go?

51:12.828 --> 51:14.623
[GIRLS CONTINUE SINGING]

51:14.657 --> 51:17.488
If she got out of the house,
this should be over.

51:17.522 --> 51:19.317
♪ Gather hands

51:19.352 --> 51:23.597
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

51:23.632 --> 51:26.842
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

51:26.876 --> 51:28.188
Eden said he was moaning...

51:29.845 --> 51:32.158
with pleasure. He's perverted.

51:33.573 --> 51:35.540
And he wants us
because we are young

51:36.783 --> 51:37.853
and we're helpless

51:39.613 --> 51:42.271
and he can keep
thinking that all he wants.

51:44.101 --> 51:48.622
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

51:48.657 --> 51:53.213
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

51:53.248 --> 51:57.631
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

51:57.666 --> 52:02.360
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

52:02.395 --> 52:07.193
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

52:07.227 --> 52:12.025
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

52:12.059 --> 52:16.202
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

52:16.236 --> 52:20.689
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

52:20.723 --> 52:25.314
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

52:25.349 --> 52:30.147
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands

52:30.181 --> 52:34.634
[VOICES DISTORTING]
♪ Ladies of the canyons
Our own land

52:34.668 --> 52:36.394
♪ No man touches us
Gather hands ♪

52:36.429 --> 52:39.742
Please, please, please, please,
please, please, please...

52:39.777 --> 52:41.848
She's brainwashing them.

52:41.882 --> 52:43.505
No, she's hypnotizing them.

52:45.334 --> 52:46.784
Friendship is propaganda.

52:48.165 --> 52:49.752
Complete cold, total trance.

52:51.133 --> 52:52.376
But, dude, Dolly...

52:53.549 --> 52:55.310
Dolly would swallow
a turd for you.

52:56.345 --> 52:58.244
I don't want Dolly
to swallow a turd.

52:58.278 --> 52:59.624
I know. [CHUCKLES]

52:59.659 --> 53:01.902
-You don't wanna see
Dolly swallow a turd.
-I know.

53:03.456 --> 53:04.802
That's why you're our hero.

53:06.907 --> 53:08.185
Don't say a hero.

53:10.566 --> 53:12.189
You kind of want
there to be a man.

53:13.466 --> 53:15.295
Anybody who's older than us.

53:17.884 --> 53:19.092
If my stepdad were here

53:19.126 --> 53:20.956
he would ground every one of us.

53:20.990 --> 53:23.752
Okay. Well, the world
beat him to it. [CHUCKLES]

53:25.857 --> 53:26.720
Get it?

53:29.723 --> 53:31.725
I know Eden made it

53:31.760 --> 53:33.486
and is looking for help.

53:33.520 --> 53:36.247
-Yeah.
-She's actually
really athletic, you know?

53:40.147 --> 53:41.666
She's also
a really good swimmer.

53:43.185 --> 53:45.601
She can hold her breath,

53:45.636 --> 53:48.949
do a hand stand underwater
for, like, five minutes.

53:48.984 --> 53:50.572
-That's crazy.
-Yeah.

53:52.953 --> 53:55.301
I bought her a bathing suit
for her birthday.

53:55.784 --> 53:56.647
Hmm.

53:58.027 --> 53:59.374
The presents.

54:02.169 --> 54:03.240
I don't know, not tonight.

54:06.415 --> 54:07.692
Yeah, another night.

54:13.077 --> 54:14.285
I just...

54:15.286 --> 54:16.563
Hold on.

55:01.746 --> 55:02.609
Oh.

55:06.164 --> 55:07.062
Kill me.

55:07.096 --> 55:10.721
I just wanted to say

55:11.929 --> 55:12.861
I'm sorry.

55:15.312 --> 55:17.106
Because I'm never
gonna see you again.

55:22.180 --> 55:23.527
I thought that we
were gonna make up.

55:24.286 --> 55:25.563
We were supposed to make up

55:26.495 --> 55:28.532
but then we didn't.

55:31.293 --> 55:32.329
And...

55:34.158 --> 55:35.573
You know, time passes

55:37.644 --> 55:39.853
and now

55:39.888 --> 55:43.788
it's like we never
knew each other.

55:46.826 --> 55:47.689
It's like...

55:48.414 --> 55:49.656
we were...

55:50.726 --> 55:52.832
never even close

55:53.246 --> 55:54.143
but we were,

55:55.110 --> 55:56.042
I remember.

55:59.252 --> 56:00.115
I...

56:03.256 --> 56:05.051
And I did
terrible things to you.

56:07.709 --> 56:11.920
I did every terrible thing

56:11.954 --> 56:13.922
I could think of to do.

56:14.888 --> 56:17.374
And at the time
I wanted to do worse.

56:18.444 --> 56:21.067
I wanted to spit in your face.

56:23.172 --> 56:24.035
I had this...

56:25.105 --> 56:27.245
I had this

56:27.280 --> 56:29.903
really clear

56:29.938 --> 56:34.908
image of me
spitting in your face.

56:39.568 --> 56:40.742
And I regret that.

56:43.365 --> 56:45.022
I'm sorry.

56:48.094 --> 56:48.957
I'm sorry.

56:50.786 --> 56:51.649
I'm sorry.

56:54.652 --> 56:55.826
[CRYING] I'm sorry.

56:56.965 --> 56:59.726
[GIRL GASPS, ECHOES]

57:17.882 --> 57:18.987
[SCREAMS]

57:31.309 --> 57:34.934
[SHOUTING] I saw him! I saw him!

57:45.047 --> 57:45.945
What did you see?

57:47.325 --> 57:48.188
I saw him.

57:50.432 --> 57:51.468
I saw the man.

58:02.686 --> 58:03.756
PIPER: Where was he?

58:04.791 --> 58:06.413
ROMY: He was under the tarp.

58:06.448 --> 58:09.071
PIPER: Blake and I were
in the cellar and we
didn't see anything.

58:09.106 --> 58:10.314
So where in the cellar was he?

58:10.348 --> 58:12.661
ROMY: I don't know.
I saw him under the tarp.

58:12.696 --> 58:14.732
PIPER: Fine, then
let's go down there

58:14.767 --> 58:16.700
and if he is there
then we'll see him.

58:17.459 --> 58:19.841
We want him to come to us.

58:20.704 --> 58:22.050
AMANDA: Why would we want that?

58:23.603 --> 58:27.193
